          "reviewBody": "School is good. My observation for the people who are looking for admission: They have admissions each year for less than 30 kids(only prekg), in which male/female ratio is 50% , in which 90% seats filled by siblings, alumni and so on. Open seats will be around 5 which goes to most influential or most eligible parents, your kids may be super bright but school does not care. If you fall into 10% remaining category keep your expectations very low on securing seat for your kid. All the very best, good luck.",
